 3 1/2 years.=0A=0AIncidentally, =E2=80=9Cfamily office=E2=80=9D is the con=
ventional name given to the exit =0Avehicle =E2=80=94 a firm that manages i=
ts founder=E2=80=99s and employees=E2=80=99 money =E2=80=94 for a hedge =0A=
fund that gets too rich. But you can think of the big multimanager hedge fu=
nds =0Alike Citadel and Millennium Management as being in competition, not =
only with =0Aeach other, but also with another group of firms like Jane Str=
eet or Hudson =0ARiver Trading. Those firms are normally called =E2=80=9Cpr=
oprietary trading firms,=E2=80=9D and =0Athey tend not to run outside inves=
tors=E2=80=99 money; their equity is normally owned =0Amostly by their foun=
ders and employees. There are broad differences between =0Amultimanager hed=
ge funds and prop firms =E2=80=94 the prop firms=E2=80=99 portfolios usuall=
y =0Aturn over faster than the hedge funds=E2=80=99 =E2=80=94 but there is =
some convergence in =0Astrategies and employees; we=E2=80=99vetalked about =
=0A<https://www.google.com/search=3Fq=3Dmatt+levine+secret+trade&oq=3Dmatt+=
