roversially hired some Jane Street traders to move their =0Astrategy to Mil=
lennium.=0A=0AYou can imagine these firms converging on a similar business =
model =E2=80=94 using =0Aleverage and technology to rapidlyprovide liquidit=
y and price discovery =0A<https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2024-0=
8-05/the-good-trades-have-gone-bad=3Fcmpid=3DBBD101724_MONEYSTUFF&utm_mediu=
m=3Demail&utm_source=3Dnewsletter&utm_term=3D241017&utm_campaign=3Dmoneystu=
ff>=0A in public markets =E2=80=94 from different starting points: The prop=
 firms grew out of =0Asmall partnerships whose basic business model was =E2=
=80=9Cdo rapid trading with our =0Aown money,=E2=80=9D while the multimanag=
er funds grew out of single-manager hedge funds =0Awhose basic business mod=
el was =E2=80=9Cinvest money for clients.=E2=80=9D But if you do either =0A=
of those things well for a long time, you might end up in the same place, =
=0Arunning similar collections of strategies and not even needing client mo=
ney.=0A=0A=0AShould index funds be illegal=3F=0A=0ANo, I=E2=80=99m kidding,=
 this isn=E2=80=99t about index funds at all. The basic idea =0A<https://ww=
w.bloomberg.com/opinion/newsletters/2018-12-07/money-stuff-regulators-ask-i=
f-index-funds-are-bad=3Fcmpid=3DBBD101724_MONEYSTUFF&utm_medium=3Demail&utm=
_source=3Dnewsletter&utm_term=3D241017&utm_campaign=3Dmoneystuff>=0A of =E2=
=80=9Cshould index funds be illegal=E2=80=9D is that an investor that owns =
shares of =0Aevery company in a sector =E2=80=94 like an index fund =E2=80=
=94 will not want too much =0Acompetition in that sector. Fierce competitio=
n will create winners and losers, =0Abut the investor will own all of them,=
 so its losses on the losers will offset =0Aits gains on the winners. Where=
as if everyone just contentedly raises prices =0Athen the investor makes mo=
ney on all of them.=0A=0AThat=E2=80=99s controversial, but if you like it y=
ou can extend the idea to new areas. =0A=E2=80=9CCommon ownership of differ=
ent companiesreduces labor market competition =0A<https://www.envoy.cirrus.=
bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2024-07-18/maybe-good-governance-is-bad=3Fcm=
pid=3DBBD101724_MONEYSTUFF&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_source=3Dnewsletter&utm_t=
erm=3D241017&utm_campaign=3Dmoneystuff>=0A,=E2=80=9D for instance, or even =
=E2=80=9Cincreases tax evasion =0A<https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articl=
es/2020-02-21/the-companies-are-on-the-same-team=3Fcmpid=3DBBD101724_MONEYS=
